text: <@U28TLDP0R> can you implement a quick “get deck” api endpoint that doesnt get cached? Something that just returns the json of a deck given a url. That way we can check these “did you get my deck” requests without manually gojng into the db
Maybe we can eventually change it into a user facing thing

Re: deckbox, they're definitely not tagging commanders differently and I can't get their filters to isolate all commander decks, so I'm just gonna tell the guy technical challenges. we can keep an eye on them though.
do you guys wanna handle this guy's question about indexing his deck then?
It does look like we haven't got it
Kinda surprised we havent gotten it. Our deck pulling has been more consistent lately.
Make a ticket for his deck url and ill look into it
Tell him we’ll look into it. While we try to pull as many decks as possible, we cant guarantee we get all of them.
